            <thetext>The generic back() method, introduced with bug #8095, works fine in most app scenarios. But when developing an app, e.g. reloading a certain page, it would be convenient for the app&#39;s back button (in the caption bar) to also work. 

Currently it can&#39;t, because no history information is available. This could also happen when a paused app is brought into foreground again. 

It would be useful to pre-define a default parent page that the back() method would use for navigation in case of an empty history.</thetext>
